Description
===========
Writes the decomposition to disk for visualization

"Original" Author
=================
Bernhard Gschaider (bgschaid@ice-sf.at)

Current Maintainer
==================
Bernhard Gschaider (bgschaid@ice-sf.at)

Documentation
=============
Run the utility IN PARALLEL on the decomposed case. After reconstruction 
there is a field "decomposition" that contains for each cell the number 
of the processor that "owns" that cell in parallel mode

Required OpenFOAM-Version (Known to work with)
==============================================
1.4.1 
1.5 
(propably works for older versions, but not tested)

Directory Contents
==================
writeDecomposition: source code of the utility
